descriptionMarkdown:
2 iron need to be placed on the same side of the belt. MUST BE A NORMAL INSERTER (or long-handed should work as well), set to A=[iron] or stack limit set to 1. the belt "loop length" must be longer than the time it takes for the tank to dip below the threshold steam steam and go back above it. The tank does not need to be attached to the whole steam network, and should be attached to one of the furthest turbines from the reactors. upgrading the belt hooked up to logic may break it.

how it works: constant combinator outputs A2, [iron]1, belt set to enable at <24000 steam and read, decider set to output A1 if steam<24000. inserter enables when A=[iron], with stack limit set to 1. so it works when both iron are on the belt, and steam is less than 24k.
title: nuclear 1 fuel circuit
